    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-04-26T19:03:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-04-26T19:03:00-05:00" n="135"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <head>135. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Sweden</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d135fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 795.00/4–2556. Confidential. Drafted by Norred; approved by Sebald;
                        and cleared with <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>, and <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss>/UNA.
                        Also sent to Bern and repeated to Seoul, London, Paris, and Tokyo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-04-26T19:03:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1956—7:03 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1145. Tokyo also pass <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>. Stockholm’s
                        1018<note n="2" xml:id="d135fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> repeated Tokyo 22 London 67 Bern 27
                    Paris 71 Seoul 19.</p>
                <p>Request Embassy Stockholm inform Swedes earliest (1) Point 4 your 1018 would not
                    reduce our difficulties with <gloss target="#t_NNSC1">NNSC</gloss> and could
                    create new problems. No reason believe Communists would not continue ignore
                    ports entry provisions of Armistice. We would either be forced focus all
                    movements in one port of entry or be subjected frequent inspection movements by
                    Czechs and Poles; (2) US suggests Swedes hold up any reply along lines reftel
                    pending result consultations US now beginning with Allies to determine suitable
                    course action.</p>
                <p>Embassy Bern requested inform Swiss Government earliest US beginning
                    consultations with Allies and would appreciate advance notice any Swiss action
                        <gloss target="#t_NNSC1">NNSC</gloss> problem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
